that lock into the strap keeping the watch secure in place given the heavy of the watch there is no need to tie it tight on the wrist i keep it a notch loose and it stays perfectly in place doesnt rub against the skin yet is not so tight that it would leave its imprint on my wrist the benefit of the big screen is that it can display more information you can custom up to item to be visible on each screen this feature was one of the main reason i bought this watch i want to see distance speed current pace and average pace it is very useful now that i have this information available so readily on one strength i switch to this model after have use the garmin forerunner for a year primarily because i want more features which the xt had compare to the the xts speed of acquire satellite is remarkably fast it has probably never taken more than seconds even if i am indoors the on the other hand almost never picked up signal indoors and took much long when outdoors this is very helpful particularly in the winter month when i wont have to stand outside my house in the cold wait for the watch to acquire accuracy compare to the forerunner and my iphone with mapmyrun software this watch is very close in terms of distance speed and other such parameter i know a lot of people want this data to be accurate to a tee but ive realize that most device tend to fall within a narrow range and that tiny difference in distance can be due to a number of factor for example i typically run a m route sometimes ill see that as and sometimes as this small a difference in distance can be due to just the side of the road i was running on honestly too small a difference to be of a workout during a bike ride or a run the watch can be set to give notification at the end of each lap you can choose what you want that lap to be be it mile or mile the type of notification can also be modify between beep vibration or both if you have to stop say at a traffic light the watch automatic pause recording and resume within about seconds once you resume the activity you can view average pace and current pace as one of the many metric view on the watch in my experience the current pace in reality is your average pace for approximate the last seconds so dont let current pace throw you off if it seem too fast or too slow at any point of the watch do not come with a cadence sensor of its own i had really hope that this would come with its own metronome and cadence feature but it doesnt the xt come with all these fancy accessory but the cost add up to around an extra as for the xt it needs to be connected to a bike sensor separate yes this was a significant lacking feature for me but i have no choice but to wait till one become available at a more reasonable price hope the garmin folks are reading the watch come a bluetooth dongle ant this can be insert into the usb hub of your macpc and it will automatic fire up the garmin ant agent software and transfer all data from the xt you can choose which workout you want to transfer it also let you delete data on the watch once youve transfer you can do this if you want to free up memory space but after month of heavy use i still havent had the need to delete any data the bluetooth dongle is one of the very few things about the xt that i didnt quite like it is way too tiny and needs to be store careful so that it doesnt get lost black color doesnt really help either i have kept it in my drawer in the original clear plastic packet that it came in this packet has a large yellow color sticker on it so its easy to find in the drawer i am still nervous about lose this tiny the ant bluetooth dongle transfer data to your garmin account which can be access on the garmin connect website the data is copious and broken down in pretty much every way you could want particularly if youre a statistics junkie i was pleasant surprise at the level of detail this software has compare to mapmyrun i use to think that was pretty good too but garmin data is better and more detailed btw you can transfer all data from your garmin connect account to mapmyrun or mapmyride account as well you can login to your account there and choose the import workout option and then select garmin from the in water this was another important feature that steer me to this watch the watch hold up great under water ive use this both in open water and in a pool i agree with other reviewer that the route map under water is far from accurate but i really dont care about the map as much as i do about speed and distance and on these two parameter the watch perform greatbattery i believe the advertise battery life is hour i havent had the need to keep the watch on for this long just yet the longest i have use this at a stretch is hour and it work just fine one feature that i find strange is that the watch automatic turn on when charge and stays on so every time you remove the watch from the charge cable remember to turn it off if you wont be use it for some time strange feature but just take get use the watch has the standard garmin connect in their charger that connect points to the watch the forerunner had connect points which made it difficult to connect the xt has two connect which are slightly easy to connect that said i would still have like to see a standard microusb or a different type of connect that would have been easy to connect but i understand the need for a proprietary charge cable that tie us to garmin charge cable onlyall in all the xt is a phenomenal watch for triathlete or runner or cyclist look for all the features that are packed in this device

title: Amazon Kindle Fire HDX Standing Polyurethane Origami Case (will only fit Kindle Fire HDX 7"), Mineral Black
description:
• Designed by Amazon to perfectly fit your Kindle Fire HDX
  • Innovative built-in Origami stand folds into landscape or portrait orientation for hands-free viewing
  • Redirects the sound from your Kindle Fire HDX speakers towards you, immersing you in the rich cinematic Dolby Digital Plus sound experience
  • Full-coverage case attaches magnetically for easy on and off, and automatically wakes and puts your Kindle to sleep by simply opening and closing the case
  • Vibrant polyurethane with a color-matched microfiber interior to protect your screen and keep it clean
